### 🚩 Flag 5: Malicious Application Identification

#### Objective  
Identify which application the attacker used to gain access to the compromised account.

#### Flag Value  
One Outlook Web

#### What to Hunt  
Successful and failed sign in records containing application display data for the compromised user.

#### Detection Strategy  
Query SigninLogs for both failed and successful sign in events tied to the user, then review AppDisplayName chronologically to isolate the application used during the intrusion.

#### KQL Query
```kql
SigninLogs
| where UserPrincipalName contains "smith"
| where ResultSignature in ("FAILURE", "SUCCESS")
| project TimeGenerated, UserPrincipalName, UserId, IPAddress, Identity, ResultSignature,
Location, ResultType, RiskLevelDuringSignIn, AppDisplayName
| order by TimeGenerated asc
```

#### Evidence

#### Why This Matters  
This identifies the service entry point and confirms the compromise was conducted through web based Microsoft 365 access rather than a local endpoint client.

