### 🚩 Flag 7: First Post Compromise Cloud Activity

#### Objective  
Find the first action the attacker took after gaining access in order to begin reconstructing the intrusion timeline.

#### Flag Value  
MailItemsAccessed followed by inbox rule creation activity

#### What to Hunt  
Cloud activity from the attacker’s IP across Microsoft 365 services, with special attention to mail access and subsequent rule creation.

#### Detection Strategy  
Query CloudAppEvents for the attacker IP address and sort chronologically to identify the earliest cloud actions taken immediately after successful access.

#### KQL Query
```kql
CloudAppEvents
| where IPAddress == "205.147.16.190"
| project TimeGenerated, AccountDisplayName, IPAddress, ActionType, Application,
RawEventData
| order by TimeGenerated asc
```

#### Evidence

#### Why This Matters  
This marks the transition from account compromise to operational abuse of the mailbox and shows immediate adversary intent to monitor or steal financial correspondence.

