### 🚩 Flag 9: Business Email Compromise Recipient Identification

#### Objective  
Determine who received the attacker’s fraudulent email after the mailbox was compromised.

#### Flag Value  
j.reynolds@lognpacific.org

#### What to Hunt  
Outbound email activity sent from the compromised mailbox and originating from the attacker IP, including subject, recipient, and delivery context.

#### Detection Strategy  
Query EmailEvents for mail sent from m.smith@lognpacific.org using the attacker’s IP to identify the recipient targeted in the BEC phase of the attack.

#### KQL Query
```kql
EmailEvents
| where SenderFromAddress == "m.smith@lognpacific.org"
| where SenderIPv4 == "205.147.16.190"
| project TimeGenerated, SenderFromAddress, SenderIPv4, RecipientEmailAddress, Subject,
To, UrlCount, EmailDirection
```

#### Evidence

#### Why This Matters  
This confirms the BEC target, the fraud delivery method, and that the malicious email was sent from an internal trusted account within the same attacker controlled session.

