## 💎 Diamond Analysis

Scattered Spider is the assessed adversary in this threat hunt. The victim was Mark Smith and LogN Pacific Financial Services, with a downstream impact on finance workflows and recipient j.reynolds@lognpacific.org. The adversary’s capabilities included MFA fatigue, malicious inbox rules, thread hijacking, and access to Exchange Online, OneDrive, and SharePoint. The infrastructure observed included IP 205.147.16.190, One Outlook Web, Firefox 147.0 on Linux, an attacker-controlled forwarding address at insights@duck.com, and a linked AAD session ID. Together, these elements form a Diamond Model profile consistent with a Scattered Spider style financially motivated BEC intrusion.

